text:
First of all I’d like to start this review by saying that I barely ever write a bad review. However for this hotel it was essential as most reviews online that are positive, are completely false and frustratingly misleading.

We arrived at Tanadewa Resort and Spa and did indeed have a very friendly greeting and were given a very tasty, traditional cake.

We were escorted to our room, that had a beautiful view and was a fair size not anything special, but not tiny. The room was clean and comfortable and I cannot fault it for a place to sleep.

Next we went to have dinner. The prices of the food were quite high but then, by 4* hotel standards, they would be nothing unusual if the quality followed the price. Both dishes were served cold. Quite surprising given we were the only guests in the restaurant. The wok dish my partner ordered was so salty anyone’s eyes would water. 

The alcohol section had me and my partner baffled. Prices of spirits were ridiculous and the selection poorer than in a hostel. Out of 4 types of “house wine” (the only type of wine on the menu), only two were available by the glass. When asked for, we were informed that no wine is available by the glass and we can only buy a bottle. Each bottle was in the range of £65+, which for mediocre wine is a joke. As an example - The Two Islands Riesling is sold for IDR 220k, while at the hotel the price is 6 times more expensive - IDR 1.2m. 500% margin on a bottle of wine?! 

When suggested, that perhaps opening a bottle and selling it by a glass would be a good idea, we were informed that it would incur extra cost making each glass £25+. Coming from London, this is shocking even for us.

The pool - the view is great and that’s pretty much the only upside. There are 6 sun loungers only so if you want to be by the pool be prepared to fight for it. Between a number of villas and 3 floors of rooms and given that the hotel is miles away from anything else, the space at the pool is a scarce resource the guests will surely fight for.

Due to the way the hotel is laid out you will only get sun rays until 1-2pm as as soon as the sun moves past its peak at noon, it hides behind the main building which then blocks the pool area. Not ideal for the keen tanners. 

The bar by the pool is not maned at all times. Me and my Partner waited around an hour for a member of staff to be seen near by the spa/pool area to get a simple drink. This was during the sun’s peak hours 11-1pm. When the bar was staffed you would be surprised to know that there were not any actual bottles, utensils or even a fridge behind it and the choice of drinks was extremely limited and over priced. On arrival we were informed that the bar by the pool closed at 6pm. This left only the restaurant area for the evening.  

The ‘rooftop bar’, again, is non existent. It’s an area under construction with no chairs, no tables or bar for that matter. It is simply a roof you can go and walk on.

Activities - When we arrived we were informed of activities but due to the newness of the hotel none of these were available, which was not advertised online. There is a schedule of activities advertised in the tv, each happening on a certain day of the week.

The yoga deck - under construction and barriered off.

Location - 10 minute taxi to Ubud. This wouldn’t be an issue if you are used to having to take taxis but considering we moved from a hotel where you could walk to Ubud this felt very isolating and frustrating as you couldn’t pop out for dinner or a drink to avoid the hotels inflated prices. There’s no local food or drink places in close proximity.

The shuttle from the hotel to Ubud runs only 3 times a day!

Overall the staff were nice and polite but severely lacked training. The hotel has still got a lot of development to go through, including construction work and that the owner needs to do his research on competition around before it truly deserves it’s supposed four star rating.

Kindest,
 
The couple who left 3 days before their original check out and received no compensation for the poorest experience they've had in Bali so far. After so many issues a refund of the days we would not be spending there would be the least the hotel could do. Disgraceful.
title: Disgraceful!

text:
Credits where credits are due! We've been visiting Bali for years and stayed in several hotels/resorts around and in Ubud, and this one was by far the best. So many hotels/resorts have five stars, but they just don't live up to the rating; however, for Tanadewa Resort & Spa Ubud, the star rating is absolutely deserved, and if it were possible, I would rate them even higher.

Location:
- The location of the hotel is not right in the Ubud centre but don't let that discourage you, it is just a short ride to the Ubud centre (the ride is not as long as shown on Google Maps), and you are away from the city noise, surrounded by beautiful nature.
- Additionally, the hotel has a shuttle to the city centre a few times a day if you don't/can't drive or don't want to pay for/order transport. In our case, the staff helped us arrange a bike rental.

Staff:
- The staff is exceptionally thoughtful, very kind, polite, and always smiling, and they go above and beyond to make sure you have everything you need and that you are happy. They genuinely care about their guests. 
- You barely notice the presence of the housekeeping staff as they seem to do their best to be quiet in the hallways and when they clean the surrounding rooms - very appreciated.
- Fast room service.

Room: 
- The rooms are beautiful and spacious (much more than in the photos), the beds are comfortable, the bathroom has all the amenities you need, and the housekeeping is doing a great job keeping the rooms and hotel in general clean. 
- We really appreciated the solid soundproofing of the rooms - I am a light sleeper, and I slept well here.

Food/Drinks:
- Breakfast is yummy, and so are lunch/dinner meals. 
- They also serve delicious cocktails/mocktails by the pool area and at the rooftop bar (both have fantastic valley views!)

Pool/Activities:
- The pool and the pool area are stunning! Beautiful views, a sufficient amount of sunbeds, and there's even a small reading corner with books to read on the upper pool deck. 
- We attended the complimentary morning yoga lesson, and it was great. We were pleasantly surprised. 

We've already booked another stay in a couple of days, which is, in our opinion, reasonable proof of how wonderful this resort is.

THANK YOU!

Maybe the closing time of the pool bar/restaurant could be a bit longer, now it's closing at 6pm.
title: My family and I absolutely loved staying at Tanadewa Resort & Spa Ubud!

text:
If I could rate this hotel higher than 5 stars, I would. We stayed here for five nights and we never wanted to leave!
Every single staff member that we interacted with was incredible! Very kind, very respectful, very courteous. At check in, you are given a traditional drink and snack. They show you to your room and they even bring your luggage to your room for you. Throughout our stay, the reception staff was lovely. We had them call us a taxi pretty much every night to go to dinner, and they were always happy to help! Also, you can have the taxi fare charged to your room, which was very convenient for saving our cash for shopping. For anyone complaining that you can’t get a Grab or Gojek and you have to take a taxi from the hotel - this is Ubud. It’s much more spaced out and rural here compared to, say, Seminyak. And, they are just doing their part in supporting the local taxi drivers! The rates are technically higher than Grab, but honestly, we were more than happy to support the local drivers and not Grab, which I’m sure takes more than a fair cut of the fare. Also, most of our drivers were super nice and offered to wait at the restaurant to drive us back to the hotel after dinner.
As for the actual hotel, our room was very spacious and comfy! We just got a king room, no villa, no private pool. But, we found it very much to our liking. I saw some reviews about the lack of toothbrush in the bathroom… but my question is, why didn’t you bring a toothbrush on your trip? Also, they make it pretty clear that if you need any extra toiletries, or really anything at all, all you have to do is ask and any one of the amazingly helpful staff can bring you what you need.
The pool was small but beautiful. It had a great view of the jungle and comfy beach chairs with umbrellas, as well as a bar where you can order food and/or drinks.
The hotel breakfast was admittedly nothing to write home about, but it was definitely satisfactory! And IMO, you can’t beat the convenience of a hotel breakfast. They had a good mix of Indonesian and western breakfast foods, both in the buffet and on the menu of breakfast items you can order. We did order room service a few times as well, and the ayam geprek sambal matah was our go to! We thought it was delicious, especially in the comfort of our hotel room.
The real star of the show for us was the spa. We went three times in five days! That’s how much we loved it. Truly, we just kept booking another appointment after each session until our literal last day in Bali. It started on our arrival day, it was quite late in the afternoon, we were lounging by the pool, and I asked if they had any more availability at the spa for that day. They told us that unfortunately, they were fully booked for the rest of the evening, but that they would call our room if anything opened up. We decided to stay at the pool and just book a session for another day. But then, the bartender at the pool came and found us to let us know there was an available appointment in a little more than an hour! We were stunned at this level of service, as it would have been completely fair of them to just call our room and give away the spot to someone else once we didn’t answer.
We tried different spa treatments each time we went, and each time it was sublime. They always start you off with some delicious fruit tea, and then you are led to your private little massage hut/room. The massage therapists were so lovely, they truly made the experience. On the first day, she noticed that I was a little bit sunburnt on my back and she made sure to extra extra take care of my skin! I also really appreciated the level of communication they encourage. Monika always asked me how the pressure was, and she always made sure that it was okay to massage my stomach, etc. They were so professional and clearly just amazing at what they do. The care they put into the ritual of it all was so appreciated by us. We were rubbed, scrubbed, masked, wrapped, and polished into pure bliss. It was so incredibly worth it to try their different packages and treatments. Each massage was unbelievable, and I was lucky enough to get the same massage therapist every time. Monika, thank you SO much for everything! I can’t even tell you how much we enjoyed the spa. After long day trips around Ubud/Bali, getting pampered at the spa was truly the height of luxury.
Overall, we loved this hotel. 10/10 would recommend.
title: MUST visit the spa!

text: We spent 3 nights here as part of a package deal that also included 4 nights at Tanadewa Villas in Nusa Dua. The resort is lovely with lush gardens and a great view from the main pool.  Our Courtyard Pool Villa was spacious and very comfortable with a large bathroom. Buffet breakfast was good and as part of our package we had 2 dinners included - the package menu is limited for choice but the dishes we did have were very tasty. We paid for dinner on the 3rd night as there is nowhere else nearby to eat, and it is a 15-20 minute drive to Ubud Centre.  The downside of that is you need to take a driver/taxi to go to Ubud Centre (the resort does run a shuttle service 3 times a day), but the upside is you are well away from the traffic and chaos of the centre and it is very quiet and peaceful. Their staff are their greatest asset - everyone was so friendly, helpful and couldn't do enough for us.  Shout out to Kaurnia in the restaurant who was amazing, not only did she remember our names every night but also what we'd eaten the night before and what we'd said we'd like to try the next night! If you want to be near all the restaurants/bars/shops etc of Ubud Centre this probably wouldn't suit but for a restful few days in a beautiful setting, I'd definitely go back.
title: Peaceful Paradise

The main pool area is also stunning and has a great view. It's big enough to swim laps and good for tanning.

The food here is really amazing. I've been all around Bali, but their bebek goreng (fried duck) is the best I've had and a dish to remember. We also had a floating breakfast (for the first time ever) and it's quite a unique experience to have a breakfast floating in your own private pool.

The location is very strategic. In 10 minutes you're in the center of Ubud, which can be quite busy. The area around Tanadewa is a bit more quiet and relaxing. It's also on the South part of Ubud, so perfect if you're coming from Uluwatu / Seminyak / Sanur.

text:
We loved our stay in early January 2020. The welcome and registration, as well as every staff person's attention to us was remarkable. Always smiling and making sure we had anything we needed, at the resort or recommendations for sight-seeing. We had hired a guide when we began our Bali visit. He suggested Tanadewa and we're really glad he did. The entire property and our experience of it met or even exceeded our expectations. Next time, we won't plan as many excursions with our guide so that we can do nothing in this idyllic and luxurious oasis in the jungle near Ubud. And their attention to their eco-footprint - no plastic water bottles, and mineral water re-fill stations, paper straws instead of plastic - GREAT!
We particularly enjoyed the gentle conversations with the dining room and bar staff, who extended our limited knowledge of courteous Balinese words. This also led to interesting conversations about local culture and customs.
Only big challenge was booking from their website, which goes to a 3rd party sight that was confusing to me. A couple of phone calls revealed different availability than the website showed. In the end, it all worked out, however it took several days of emails and payment authorizations. I was nervous that we'd lose our room choice.
I wouldn't hesitate about staying at Tanadewa next time we visit Bali. It's a hidden gem!!
title: relax in paradise - exceptional hospitality

text:
We stayed over Christmas 2019. I loved the resort from the minute we arrived. I was appreciative of the local Bali treats and ginger tea they gave us upon arrival. The cold cloth was refreshing as well. We stayed in a Villa and my main reason for selecting it was for the private pool. Our room was not quite ready yet so we grabbed some lunch in their restaurant. Once our room was ready They escorted us from the lobby down to our villa via golf cart and our luggage had already been transferred to the villa. The villa pool was much cooler than the main pool though, so we didn’t use it quite as much as we thought we would. We traveled with 2 children. Ages 4 and 2. The room was large enough that it didn’t feel super crowded. It was very clean (minus a few ants in the bathroom) and the bed was very comfortable. The view from our room was greenery and distant jungle. No buildings or other people. The breakfast buffet was delicious and we had the french toast every morning. The kids loved the chocolate muffins and the fresh juices as well. Their lunch and dinner menu is delicious and offered kid friendly choices too.

I tried out the spa and selected the 3 hour “Grounding Realm” package. I went at 6pm so I could go right back and fall asleep. I LOVED it! I was in my own private villa with rain shower and soaking tub. the package included a foot soak, massage, body scrub, body mask and facial. My villa was right next to the pool so for a little while I could hear kids playing in the pool but they eventually left and all was peaceful. At the end they offered a tray of ginger tea, sweets and local fruit. The experience was relaxing and just what I needed. You could hear the frogs and even a distant thunderstorm coming!

The staff offer a shuttle Several times during the day to and from downtown Ubud. We used there service 3 times. Air conditioned vans and very comfortable. All of the staff was very friendly and helpful. 
Overall our experience was great! I would love to go back and highly recommend Tanadewa Resort.

text:
We booked this hotel a few months ago, and had started to get a little worried after reading a number of the bad reviews. It’s definitely no where near as bad some of the reviews have made out, but I wouldn’t say it meets up to my experiences of a 5 star hotel. 

The hotel - the hotel is beautiful, and looks exactly like the pictures. We stayed in a suite, and it was a very large room with large bathroom, and beautiful balcony overlooking the valley. The pool is beautiful, but there are only 6 sun loungers. They have put out some beanbags for people to lay on to make up for this, and we never struggled to get somewhere to sit by the pool, but the bean bags weren’t that comfy. 

The location - the hotel is located about 7km from the centre of Ubud, and the hotel puts on a shuttle 4 x per day. It’s not expensive in a taxi (100k-150k IDR) to get back late at night. The advantage of it being further out of Ubud, is that it is so calm and peaceful. Definitely needed after how busy Ubud was! The disadvantage is that you have to plan ahead what you want to do. 

Food and drink - breakfast everyday was great, there was quite a lot of choice to order as well as additional items to self serve. We had some lunch and dinner in the hotel; the food was lovely, but really expensive by Bali standards. For example, we shared a starter and had a main meal and a large beer each, and it came to 700,000 IDR. In Ubud, we would be eating the same meal for approx 200,000 IDR. The hotel are doing it as they know they have a captive audience, but I think it could have been a bit less expensive. 

Things which could be improved:
- there seems to be quite a lot of maintenance work still going on, which is quite disruptive. 
- a later shuttle into and back from Ubud - the last shuttle is at 18.30 back to the hotel. 
- a bar/social area. As the hotel is so far from Ubud, it would have been nice to enjoy a drink in the evening somewhere social in the hotel.
- the fridge in the room and the light switches all have blue LED lights on, which are really bright, and made it difficult to sleep at night. 
- the air con in the rooms is really loud. Hahahahaha 
- my partner had a massage and it wasn’t the best, the therapist was quite rough, and didn’t adapt even when he asked for her to be more gentle (this could just be personal preference though). 

All in all, I would say it is definitely worth staying here, but the hotel has a bit further to go before fully deserving it’s 5 star status - I would say it is closer to 4 stars.
title: Not quite 5 star yet

A hidden jewel in Ubud’s valley…
I had stayed with my friends for a weekend and I really had a very delightful and wonderful time during my stay. First of all the lobby, when you enter the lobby you will be captivated by the magnificent scenery Should you stay here, please make sure to wake up at sunrise and take lots of pictures, do it from the bridge on the 5th floor. We stayed in the presidential suite and the room is sooo lovely, sooo spacious (the bathroom is also sooo spacious), the bathtub is huge and it has its own living room with sofa bed, its super clean with a lovely fragrance, it has espresso machine that can make a really good coffee (love this little detail), and the most important thing is the view. I ordered caesar salad not expecting much but when I ate it, the dressing, the chicken and the veggies was perfectly seasoned and it just blow my expectation. In result, instead of trying restaurants in Ubud we prefer to eat dinner at Tanarasa every night.. hehehe. Last but not least, the spa, Tanaspa, you should try the spa there. text:
I understood that the hotel just opened in March this year. So there is still some minor renovation going on, but it didn't bother me as it was on the main lobby level away from my villa. Overall, I'm quite happy with the room. The layout of the room with the pool right in front of the bed and the view of the beautiful lush greenery really make this a relaxing holiday.

I understand the resort is full due to the peak season but I don't see many other guests around. It is a boutique resort with limited number of rooms. The private pool is also relatively good size with a depth of about 1 meter or more roughly I believe. I did not use the main pool but did went to take a photo and it is beautiful. The resort sits on a low hill overlooking a small valley.

You do hear cricket sound at night but that is just part of being in nature. 

I was a solo female traveller, and I feel completely safe. Booked directly with the hotel online so it came with a one-way airport transfer. My driver was waiting for me when I arrived at the airport and he was professional. The ride from the international airport takes about slightly less than 2 hours, but it all depends on the traffic. I exited the airport at 2pm on a Friday just to give some perspective.

While for breakfast - you order cooked-food from the menu and there are salad, yogurt and juices on buffet style. No complaint on breakfast.

The only downside is the free yoga session happens only on Wed morning. But I was there for a quick weekend get-away so it would be great if they can offer yoga on weekend instead. They do have a nice pavilion for yoga which you can use for private yoga session. 

There are four complimentary shuttle to and back from Ubud town centre daily and it is roughly about 5/6km depending to the centre which takes about roughly 20 mins depending on traffic-condition. But August is supposedly the peak so taxi rides are triple the price between IDR 100,000 to IDR 150,000. I managed to find a good driver who offer to pick me up and drive me to town for IDR100,000 and to the airport for IDR 350,000. The hotel charges IDR 450,000. In the end, I negotiated a package price including the ride to airport. And I just had to send him a WhatsApp message 15 min before the pick up time and he/his friend will come and pick me up.

text:
I stayed at a villa in the Tanadewa Resort and Spa Ubud for three nights with my partner. Although the facilities are beautiful it didnt live up to what my expectations of a 5 star resort would be. 

Firstly, we had issues with the taxi situation. Reception staff never warned us that grab/online taxis are not allowed in ubud due to the “save the culture” movement which was eventually explained to us by one of the very kind shuttle drivers. There is a group of approx 10 drivers that sit outside the resort at all times of the day and night ensuring that no one arrives in an online taxi without hassle and it was unnerving coming back from tours with drivers staring in at you as they knew you weren’t with a local driver. The shuttle service is restricted by the poor pick up/drop off times with the last drop off into ubud leaving the hotel at 6pm. Reception staff really need to give advice on how to get back to the hotel at night as we were a bit clueless our first night and overpaid for a taxi back. (Should only be 100-120K)

Secondly, there was ants/spiders all over the villa we were staying in and the ants were particularly bad around the sink area.

Finally, the biggest shortcoming of this resort is its service. As a resort that rivals any European resort prices we were expecting a lot. We waited 40 minutes for a cappuccino at the pool bar the first day. The restaurant was extremely bad value for money. We paid over 600K for two very average starters and two mains with no alcohol on the first night and waited for a long time in an empty restaurant (unsurprising). If you are staying here please do yourself a favour and head into ubud for much more action and value for money. Breakfast was fine nothing special but the buffet section is very poor and coffee was awful. I would also have to say that we noticed several other guests to be at the least mildly irritated and at most agitated both at breakfast and in the reception area which wasn’t a good sign. Staff are nice but very soul less. We weren’t asked about our stay as we checked out and we were given an incorrect bill.

The activities also left much to be desired. Being from Ireland I would associate yoga with Bali and was very disappointed to see that it is only provided by the hotel once a week on a Wednesday from 7-8am. Fortunately our three night stay overlapped with that but many people wouldn’t be as lucky. Most of the activities also come with an additional cost.

The room was very clean and the infinity pool is beautiful (if you manage to get one of the six beds) but as the place we had hoped to be the highlight of our Bali trip, we were left very disappointed.
title: Very disappointing

text:
Before going to Tanadewa, we were little bit worried because of some bad comments made to this hotel. But how surprised we were when we get there! It is totally AMAZING hotel!
From the beggining.
LOCALISATION:of this hotel is YES, 6 km from Ubud centre, but when you make reservation for this hotel, you know it and it is not a surprise. They have shuttle service to the Ubud centre 3 or 4 times a day and also return shuttle 3 times a day. You can reach Ubud centre by taxi, which always stay in the front of hotel (we paid 100k for one way). Way is about 15-20 min.
HOTEL: is newly opened, so everything is clean, new:) Very nice people in reception and whole hotel staff was also nice, smiled and helpful. View from reception hall is stunning-you can see whole jungle valley, with little nice rice fields on the top. They have some activities-yoga once a week, also small fit gym is available. Whole area of hotel is very green (how did they do it when hotel is new??), with many trees, some palmtrees and other green plants. Swimming pool is nice, not very big, but also not to small. But places for sunbathing..They do not have umbrellas and also just a few sunbeds (I think that there are 6 sunbeds but they realise it is too small for this hotel and add additional big beans, but still not umbrellas). For people who want to use pool and getting tan, we recommend to have villa with pool.
ROOM: We stayed at villa with pool, so we do not know much about rooms, and we just will describe villa. First of all we asked for nice view villa and we were amazed by villa with view we get! It was totally super cool, with the best view to the green valley. Pool has it own big sunbeds (this cocoon type), was covered by green plants so that we can feel privacy when resting and tanning during the day. Inside villa we have very big room, with good air conditioning, and good and quiet windmill, which we often used. Bathroom was very big, with tube with nice view, two washbasin, big mirrors, and shower. There were many amenities available-all you need, even salt for tube. 
ROOM SERVICE: They cleaned our room twice a day! Also daily water bottles available. Coffee maker with capsules. No problem to reach reception when you need help.
FOOD: very nice breakfast (a la carte, but you can pick more than one dish, so there is no way you will stay hungry!). Also little additional items available in buffet (some croissants, jams, fruits etc). Good balinese coffee (this mud type coffe, but this is balinese coffee and it is great!). We eat also dinner in restaurant and all the food was great with reasonable prices.

To sum up: GREAT hotel with breathtaking view, but remember that is is not near centre. We recommend to have poll villa, when you plan to use swimming pool often. We do not feel that there were any bad issue which we can write.
Higly recommend!

text:
Nous avons séjourné 4 nuits au sein de cet hôtel récemment ouvert. Nous avons séjourné en villa avec piscine privée au mois de juillet. 

Points forts : 
- Hôtel très calme, reposant
- Belle piscine privée, belle chambre
- Prix très attractif
- Produit spray et prise anti moustique fournie
- Bouteilles d'eau fournies quotidiennement

Points faibles :
- Nous avons été très déconcertés par la "mafia" de taxis autorisée et entretenue par l'hôtel qui bloque tous les services de taxi souhaitant venir récupérer des clients à l'hôtel afin de proposer leurs tarifs (très élevés) ! Certains taxis sont mêmes devenus agressifs envers nous lorsque nous leur avons dit que nous souhaitions prendre un taxi en ligne. 
- Nous avions un gecko qui faisait des bruits terribles la nuit et nous réveillait en sursaut. Nous avions prévenu la réception qui n'a pas su résoudre le problème, nous n'avons donc pas passé de très bonnes nuits. 
- Gros problème de management, le service n'est pas à la hauteur (nous avions par exemple commandé un floating breakfast et il est arrivé très en retard avec beaucoup de choses manquantes alors que nous avions fait notre demande la veille)
- Service de navette vers le centre d'Ubud pas du tout au point, une fois que la navette nous a déposés, elle n'est jamais revenue nous chercher et nous avons dû payer un taxi retour (qui nous a heureusement été remboursé par l'hôtel)
- Chaussons en chambre en "paille" pas très hygiénique 
- Notre villa avait beaucoup de vis-à-vis, faire attention lors de la réservation, demander une villa en hauteur sans vis-à-vis
- Piscine privée assez froide, dommage qu'elle ne soit pas chauffée
- Il y a très peu de place autour de la piscine privée, c'est dommage car impossible de s'allonger sur un transat ou autre pour bronzer
- La terrasse est envahie de fourmis
- Chaleur de la douche assez approximative, beaucoup de variations
- Villa jamais réellement fermée, les portes ne se ferment pas complètement ce qui fait que des petites bêtes peuvent rentrer à tout moment dans la chambre 
- Aucune machine de retrait d'argent disponible à l'hôtel...

L'hotel et les villas avec piscines privées sont très bien mais le service mérite d'être amélioré pour offrir des prestations dignes d'un hôtel 5*.
title: Bien mais...

text:
Чудесный новый отель. Персонал настолько услужлив и участлив что невольно запоминаешь всех по именам .  Очень комфортно и чисто! Номера соответствуют фото. 

Завтраки шикарные. Шведский стол каждый день меняется + выбор 2х горячих блюд по меню. Очень вкусно! 

Интересные активитис - очень понравилось. И экскурсии и мастер-классы и урок музыки. Есть как бесплатные, так и платные . 

Единственный минус- это сложно найти свободный лежак у бассейна. Так как постояльцы занимают как можно больше и разнообразнее лежаков и нигде не лежат. Просто раскладывают свои вещи и уходят. Это раздражает, но это проблема не в отеле , а в менталитете постояльцев. Вид из бассейна красивый , на ущелье и речку. Но там сейчас что-то строят. Наверное в будущем будет ещё красивее. 

До центра города ходит бесплатный  шаттл с удобным расписанием в течении дня,  туда и обратно.  Сервис в отеле просто великолепный. Хочется возвращаться снова. Есть услуга трансфера на комфортном авто и гольф-кар для передвижения по территории отеля. Хоть территория совсем компактная, но с большими перепадами высот и с большим количеством ступенек. Поэтому это очень актуально. 

Есть услуга завтрак в бассейне( платно). Огромный поднос с обильным выбором блюд помещают прямо в воду, поручается очень красивая фотосессия . 

В каждом номере есть балкон. Но курить на территории отеля запрещено. Можно только на улице около рецепшн и в уличном ресторане на веранде . Больше нигде. 

На каждом этаже есть кулер. В номерах предоставляются халаты, тапочки , зубные наборы, лосьон и прочие банные принадлежности. Фен и чайник. Не очень удобный шкаф, всего одна полочка для одежды получается, но такой дизайн. Зато есть просторный диван .  В номере много освещения , ламп и светильников. Это огромный плюс и большая редкость на Бали , почему-то. Есть один русский канал- «Россия» . Уборка номера дважды в день. Очень чисто ! Не придраться ! 

Есть своя охраняемая парковка . И библиотека .  

Приветственный напиток co сладостями  и подарок при check out ))))
title: Новый отель
